        "title": "fix(cli): harden Windows node pairing and approvals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve existing untagged device tokens for same-key metadata refresh approvals when the token was already valid before approval\n- keep rotating for scope expansion, public-key repair, stale baseline tokens, revoked/issuer-tagged tokens, incompatible role/scopes, and malformed persisted token entries\n- make devices/nodes/gateway CLI RPC helpers use the direct local gateway-client admin path for explicit loopback token/password auth, avoiding stale paired CLI identity/scope traps\n- make `approvals get --node` tolerate host-native Windows exec policy payloads instead of crashing on the local approvals-file shape\n- harden stable Windows node identity/event routing, node approval RPC authz, explicit loopback shared-token probing, and pending node-list presentation\n\n## Draft Snapshot\nCurrent pushed draft head: `92e06dfe72015eecdba616bbb859d378512bd827`.\n\nThis branch is rebased onto current `main` and GitHub reports it as mergeable. The latest reviewer follow-up fixed the lower-level explicit loopback shared-token probe so configured local SecretRefs are resolved with config-first precedence instead of being shadowed by stale `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN` env fallback.\n\n## Proof On Current Head\n- Focused regression: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/call.test.ts` passed 97 tests.\n- Focused pairing/auth smoke: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/call.test.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts src/cli/gateway-rpc.runtime.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/call.test.ts src/cli/devices-cli.runtime.timeout.test.ts src/cli/program.nodes-basic.e2e.test.ts` passed 4 Vitest shards.\n- Targeted lint: `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.ts src/cli/direct-loopback-gateway-auth.test.ts` passed.\n- Autoreview: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n\n## Known Validation Blocker\n- `GOMAXPROCS=2 CI=true OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 pnpm check:changed` currently fails in `lint core` after 911s because `typescript/no-unsafe-type-assertion` fires repo-wide across unrelated shards (`src/acp`, `src/agents`, `src/config`, `src/gateway`, `ui`, `packages`, etc.). This branch does not change lint config, package manifests, lockfile, or lint scripts. Typecheck lanes skipped only for sparse checkout missing `ui/config`, per the repo sparse-safe path.\n\n## Earlier Pond Proof\n- Earlier Azure pond proof on prior draft head `aec31cb62ba9e69314ab5a7b84d4049a38a10eea`: Linux gateway plus two signed Windows `v0.6.0-alpha.14` nodes connected, pairing converged, pending=0, paired=2, commandlessPaired=0, exec allow/deny worked, and safe feature smoke covered `system.which`, `device.info`, `device.status`, `camera.list`, and `screen.snapshot`.\n- Signed prerelease asset used for the Windows proof: `OpenClawCompanion-Setup-x64.exe`, release `v0.6.0-alpha.14`, digest `sha256:36405bd72e2c11bae0aa051b551b339982a66ffb59820d977ad9983dbf0b4d98`.\n\n## Still Draft\n- Need rerun/resolve full changed validation once the repo-wide oxlint issue is understood.\n- Need refresh the Azure pond gateway to current head and reverify pairing + exec approvals with the signed Windows nodes.",
